{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17599203","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17599203"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T11:50:11+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T11:50:11+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15530"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"15530","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/15530"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.73,0.05,0.09,0,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8221"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61751"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"8221","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/8221"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15530"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47197"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"4929"},{"type":"tags","id":"4941"},{"type":"tags","id":"4942"},{"type":"tags","id":"4949"},{"type":"tags","id":"5322"},{"type":"tags","id":"7001"},{"type":"tags","id":"7004"},{"type":"tags","id":"7607"},{"type":"tags","id":"9877"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"19881"},{"type":"contributions","id":"19885"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61751","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/61751"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe pituitary gland has distinct anterior and posterior regions with different embryological origins and regulatory mechanisms.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following statements correctly describes the posterior pituitary gland?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Stores and releases antidiuretic hormone","Is also called the adenohypophysis","Receives regulatory hormones via the portal system","Produces its own hormones locally","Contains hormone-producing cells"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe \u003Cstrong\u003Eposterior pituitary\u003C/strong\u003E (neurohypophysis) stores and releases hormones that are produced in the hypothalamus - specifically antidiuretic hormone (ADH) and oxytocin. These hormones travel down nerve axons from the hypothalamus.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe term \u003Cstrong\u003Eadenohypophysis\u003C/strong\u003E refers to the anterior pituitary, not the posterior portion. The \u003Cstrong\u003Eportal system\u003C/strong\u003E delivers regulatory hormones to the anterior pituitary only. The posterior pituitary does not \u003Cstrong\u003Eproduce its own hormones\u003C/strong\u003E locally, nor does it \u003Cstrong\u003Econtain hormone-producing cells\u003C/strong\u003E - it only stores and releases hormones made in the hypothalamus.\u003C/p\u003E        \u003Cp\u003EThe posterior pituitary is actually an extension of neural tissue, while the anterior pituitary develops from oral ectoderm (Rathke\u0027s pouch).\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The posterior pituitary (neurohypophysis) stores and releases antidiuretic hormone and oxytocin produced in the hypothalamus","The posterior pituitary receives hormones directly via nerve axons, not through the portal system","The anterior pituitary (adenohypophysis) receives regulatory hormones via the hypothalamic-hypophyseal portal system"],"references":["Das L, Vaiphei K, Rai A, Ahuja CK, Singh P, Mohapatra I, Chhabra R, Bhansali A, Radotra BD, Grossman AB, Korbonits M, Dutta P. Posterior pituitary tumours: patient outcomes and determinants of disease recurrence or persistence. Endocr Connect. 2021 Apr;10(4):387-400. doi: 10.1530/EC-20-0621. PMID: 33709954; PMCID: PMC8142326.","Kovacs, W. J., \u0026 Ojeda, S. R. (Eds.). (2012). Textbook of endocrine physiology. OUP USA.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47197"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"15530"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"47197","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/47197"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-11-16T13:08:09+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-11-16T13:08:43+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"8221"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"61751"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"71","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/71"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Junior","synonyms":null,"description":"Suitable for a junior, pre-clinical medical student","position":0,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"6"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"74","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/74"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Level I","synonyms":null,"description":"Remember (identifying and retrieving information)","position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"7"}},"heading":{"data":null}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"4929","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/4929"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf6d","name":"Endocrine","syn